$ ISO 12207

Systems and software engineering – → development/SDLC[Software life cycle processes].

The goal of ISO 12207 is to define a common language for
  • buyers
  •  suppliers
  •  developers
  •  maintainers
  •  operators
  •  managers
  •  technicians
involved with the software development can communicate.

ISO 12207 defines
  • 23 processes (three types: basic, supportive and organizatonal)
  • 95 activities
  • 325 tasks
  • 224 outcomes
  • 43 system and software processes

